After being on duty at Doncaster on Saturday afternoon, he flies to Ireland to ride his French Derby winner The Grey Gatsby for Kevin Ryan — successful with Salateen on Wednesday — in his re-match with International Stakes conqueror Australia in the Irish Champion Stakes at the Curragh at 6.50pm.

On Sunday, Moore will bein action at Longchamp.

RICHARD HANNON has booked leading Irish jockey Pat Smullen to ride Osaila in Sunday’s Group One Moyglare Stud Stakes at the Curragh.

 

